    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-8 ftco-animate">
          <h2 class="mb-3">Make your own unique portfolio Website</h2>
          <p>Showcase your work online with a personal portfolio, creating your own portfolio is a good way of growing
            your online presence.</p>
          <p>Having it online as a website makes it possible for people all over the world to find you. The design of a
            portfolio will give an impression to the reader of who you are. Make sure that it appears in a good and
            presentable way.</p>
          </p>
          <p>In the following lines i will explain how yu can create one</p>
          <h2 class="mb-3 mt-5">Step 1: Choose Between Manual Coding or a Website Builder</h2>
          <p>
            Once you decide what type of online portfolio you want to build, your next step is to choose whether you
            should build that website yourself or use a website builder. If youâ€™re not a coder, the best choice will be
            to use a website builder like WordPress, Squarespace or Wix. These companies offer templates and make it
            easy to showcase your work online in a straightforward way. If you build a one-page website, it will be easy
            to do using these templates.
            <img src="img/wordpress-589121_1920.jpg" alt="" class="img-fluid">
          </p>
          <h2 class="mb-3 mt-5">Step 2: Create a github account</h2>
          <p>Go to https://github.com/join . Type a user name, your email address, and a password. Choose Sign up for
            GitHub, and then follow the instructions.</p>
          <p>Follow the instructions to create a repository for your portfolio.</p>
          <h2 class="mb-3 mt-5">Step 3: Edit your website</h2>
          <p>Using a code editer or dircetly in github edit your website by entering information about you and the
            services uou provide for potential clients.</p>
          <h2 class="mb-3 mt-5">Step 4: Host the site online using github</h2>
          <p>Use git hub commands to host your site Online</p>
          <p>-Use the command git add -all in your terminal to add all styles, html and images files you have added </p>
          <img src="img/Screen Shot 2022-08-04 at 13.50.59.png" alt="" class="img-fluid">
          <p>-Use the command git rm -all unnecessary files in your terminal to remove all the files you have not used
            for the sites </p>
          <img src="img/Screen Shot 2022-08-04 at 13.57.56.png" alt="" class="img-fluid">
          <p>-Use the git command git status to verify that the compilation had no problem, if the result is red you
            have a problem in the contrary everything went alright </p>
          <img src="img/Screen Shot 2022-08-04 at 14.09.48.png" alt="" class="img-fluid">
          <p>-Use the git command git commit -m + a label of your choice to apply the modifications to the site </p>
          <img src="img/Screen Shot 2022-08-04 at 14.15.22.png" alt="" class="img-fluid">
          <p>-Finaly, use the command git push to host the site on the internet </p>
          <img src="img/Screen Shot 2022-08-04 at 14.17.55.png" alt="" class="img-fluid">
        </div>
        <div class="tagcloud">
